<subSubSection id="A03BC3990A3222A4D650DE3D083027D7" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="differential diagnosis">
<paragraph id="2B60485F3B561A9EA1942EA943E7E322" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Differential diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3E27842B3FC124AD2E45F7B37C95E196" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
The female of 
<taxonomicName id="C2713A8052B273A07A28AEC5BC56ABCE" authorityName="Hull" authorityYear="1941" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Mesembrius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Mesembrius maculifer" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maculifer">
<emphasis id="262CEBCDD460F9838D7B588018914598" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Mesembrius maculifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
cannot be confused with any other species by the reddish-brown colour of tergite II with a pair of cream-coloured slender maculae. The male is unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
