<subSubSection id="49B3630AB2DEAFFF990893C467E7BDD5" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph id="1D9857E07276A00ED92EB886F006DBD9" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Re-description female</paragraph>
<paragraph id="19673AC6428CD2BF15D9269C2DAE8057" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="10ABCF883CCBDDF13D69152407F85275" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="A913843124D8D05F087850C9A885B7FE" captionStart="Figures 33, 34" captionStartId="F17" captionText="Figures 33, 34. Mesembrius spp., habitus, lateral view 33 M. maculifer Hull (♀) 34 M. madagascariensis Keiser (♀)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1046.57052.figures33-34" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/557478" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">33</figureCitation>
).
</emphasis>
Body length: 11.2 mm. Wing length: 8.7 mm. (Only female paratype measured).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3DA7E25BF229D3E7C47FBECA1E975885" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="1F7D44B2A46E709A0B4E232C9226BF23" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Head</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="30A1F718648C1C92DA4C07516DEFCF66" captionStart="Figures 70–74" captionStartId="F28" captionText="Figures 70 - 74. Mesembrius spp., head, frontal view 70 M. capensis (Macquart) (♀) 71 M. cyanipennis (Bezzi) (♀) 72 M. chapini Curran (♀) 73 M. maculifer Hull (♀) 74 M. morio (Bezzi) (♀)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1046.57052.figures70-74" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/557489" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">73</figureCitation>
). Eyes bare, dichoptic. Face chocolate-brown to mahogany-red. Frons with ventral 2/3 light yellow-brown pilose. Face very short reddish pubescent; sparsely long pale pilose. Ocellar triangle bare. Frontal triangle with a transverse band of dark pile. Occiput chocolate-brown to mahogany-red; thick dark brown pilose. Antenna dark reddish-brown; arista paler.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A89E662C2906807F564CE82B5BE01E78" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="8AC1C382E6DCFA3BC32D593147D7E2BD" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Thorax.</emphasis>
Dull black; lateral margins and scutellum very dark red; pleurites black; reddish-orange pilose. Scutellum dull black; white pilose.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F0A4C7A37D150241F11E429257624240" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="0A7840814FEC20164D93B0FE022751B0" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Legs.</emphasis>
Predominantly black, the distal part of the pro- and mesolegs dark red; all tibiae dark red; all tarsi black dorsally, the hind pair rather flattened. Pile pale whitish on tarsi and tibiae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0BC80131FBC575270D837E9F1E46CFFC" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="729D055CE062562C29D61F1565339663" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Wing</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="F2B738F4F8664C52DAA17B0B533E91B4" captionStart="Figures 135–138" captionStartId="F41" captionText="Figures 135 - 138. Mesembrius spp., right wing 135 M. maculifer Hull (♀) 136 M. madagascariensis Keiser (♂) 137 M. minor (Bezzi) (♂) 138 M. morio (Bezzi) (♀)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1046.57052.figures135-138" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/557502" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">135</figureCitation>
). Proximal half of the wing deep brown, especially at the r-m crossvein.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E66A5BEB8FF4D1A0F554D1DD0779DAD0" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="C705EB0B9FC9964D439211ECE8839411" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Abdomen</emphasis>
(Fig. 
